post_text:
On the eve of Back to School 2020, please know that we have waited five long months to see the smiling faces of our students back on campus. The Pirate crew has worked nonstop to ensure that everything is ready both virtually and blended. From curriculum, to safety, from PPE to disinfectant, from new floors to new technology, WE ARE READY! Please know that we are anxious to see all of you during our transition days Monday and Tuesday and looking forward to the best year ever kicking off on Wednesday! Our leadership team has planned and coordinated around the clock to ensure we are prepared! We are in this TOGETHER! We have everyone covered from masks, to school supplies, water bottles to chrome books and much, much more! Please know how amazing your Pirate crew is and how excited we are to sail off into 2020-2021!
#WeChooseHappy #Together #PirateNation

Governor Hutchinson and Secretary Key applauds the work of schools and thanks teachers, students and families today and announced that the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year will finalized through digital instruction with no on-site delivery for the remainder of the year.

We will be continuing our work as we have outlined this last week moving forward through the end of our regularly planned calendar (May 21). As always, if you need assistance please let us know. We consistently are here and willing to support as we can. The key is flexibility, support and understanding, so those are core strengths we will be reinforcing in the days ahead.

As previously posted, Prom and Graduation is postponed and will be scheduled at a later date once we are able. Additionally, the AAA will be providing information soon regarding other spring activities/sports.

Thanks to all of you and stay well.
We are here as needed!
#ALLmeansALL

post_text:
The District is continuing to monitor updates regarding COVID-19 and is receiving continual guidance from the (ADH) Arkansas Department of Health and the Division of Elementary and Secondary Education (DESE). Additionally, the Governor signed an executive order today that stated that ‚Äúthe Secretary of Health, in consultation with the Secretary of Education, shall have sole authority to close public school campuses throughout the state for reasons related to COVID-19."

As a reminder, the best way to protect from contracting any virus is by practicing healthy habits, washing your hands frequently and thoroughly, and keeping students home if not feeling well. Our nursing staff is doing an incredible job of taking care of our students and will be notifying parents of any concerns as normal. In addition our rooms and buildings are being cleaned and sanitized on an ongoing basis.

Please also note the travel guidance as we near spring break. If you have specific questions or concerns, please contact the Office of the Superintendent. Thank you in advance!
text:
The District is continuing to monitor updates regarding COVID-19 and is receiving continual guidance from the (ADH) Arkansas Department of Health and the Division of Elementary and Secondary Education (DESE). Additionally, the Governor signed an executive order today that stated that ‚Äúthe Secretary of Health, in consultation with the Secretary of Education, shall have sole authority to close public school campuses throughout the state for reasons related to COVID-19."

As a reminder, the best way to protect from contracting any virus is by practicing healthy habits, washing your hands frequently and thoroughly, and keeping students home if not feeling well. Our nursing staff is doing an incredible job of taking care of our students and will be notifying parents of any concerns as normal. In addition our rooms and buildings are being cleaned and sanitized on an ongoing basis.

Please also note the travel guidance as we near spring break. If you have specific questions or concerns, please contact the Office of the Superintendent. Thank you in advance!

post_text:
Did you know the Greenland School District is now enrolling? How about having an option to School Choice into our district?

School Choice Application deadline is quickly approaching. Please submit by May 1.

We have many innovative programs, clubs and activities to offer. Your student could be included in literacy and intervention planning, personalized and flexible learning, as well as many exciting electives. Art, Agriculture, Family and Consumer Science as well as Drama too! Even online and virtual class options, concurrent and college credit courses all on our campus and with a caring and supporting staff. Come be part of the Pirate Nation, #ALLmeansALL.

Greenland Pirates gain access to athletic activities and clubs such as:

Football
Basketball
Cross Country
Track
Baseball
Softball
Dance
Cheer

EAST
Robotics
FCCLA

NHS
